.TH "blk_queue_physical_block_size" 9 "blk_queue_physical_block_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blk_queue_physical_block_size \- set physical block size for the queue
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" blk_queue_physical_block_size
.BI "(struct request_queue *q "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "q" 12
the request queue for the device
.IP "size" 12
the physical block size, in bytes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This should be set to the lowest possible sector size that the
hardware can operate on without reverting to read-modify-write
operations.
